Replacing Values for Better Understanding

In [ ]:
df['Sex'].replace({1:'Male',0:'Female'},inplace=True)

df['Chest Pain Type'].replace({0:'asymptomatic',1: 'atypical angina', 2: 'non-anginal pain',3: 'typical angina'},inplace=True)

df['Fasting Blood_Sugar'].replace({1:'True',0:'False'},inplace=True)

df['RestECG'].replace({0:'Estes criteria',1: 'normal', 2: 'Having ST-T wave abnormality'},inplace=True)

df['Induced_angina'].replace({0:'No',1:'Yes'},inplace=True)

df['slope'].replace({0: 'downsloping',1: 'flat', 2: 'upsloping'},inplace=True)

df['thal'].replace({0:'Null', 1:'fixed defect', 2: 'normal blood flow',3: 'reversible defect' },inplace=True)

df['target'].replace({0:'No',1:'Yes'},inplace=True)

Outlier Detection

In [ ]:
#Visualising Outliers
 
lst=[i for i in df.columns]
plt.figure(figsize=(13,17))
i=1
for it in range(len(lst)):
    
    if df[lst[it]].dtype!="object":
        plt.subplot(3,2,i)
        plt.title(lst[it].upper())
        #plt.xlabel(lst[it]+" Range")
        sns.boxplot(data=df[lst[it]],color='r',orient='h')
        i+=1

plt.show()
Outlier Correction
In [ ]:
#Droping null values in thal
df.drop(df.index[(df['thal']=='Null')==True],axis=0,inplace=True)
In [ ]:
#Droping uneven values values in cholesterol,no of blood vessels,oldpeak
df.drop(df.index[df['Cholesterol']>350],axis=0,inplace=True)

df.drop(df.index[df['The number of major vessels']>3],axis=0,inplace=True)

df.drop(df.index[df['oldpeak']>4],axis=0,inplace=True)

Distribution of values¶

In [ ]:
lst=[i for i in df.columns]
plt.figure(figsize=(13,42))
i=1
for it in range(len(lst)):
    
    if df[lst[it]].dtype!="object":
        plt.subplot(6,2,i)
        plt.title(lst[it].upper())
        #plt.xlabel("Density")
        plt.xlabel(lst[it]+" Range")
        sns.boxenplot(data=df[lst[it]],color='y',orient='h')
        i+=1
        plt.subplot(6,2,i)
        plt.title(lst[it].upper())
        plt.xlabel("Density")
        plt.ylabel(lst[it]+" Range")
        sns.distplot(df[lst[it]],color='blue')
        i+=1

plt.show()

Observations and Results

  • Females are most affected by the Heart Disease (Angina)
  • People at the middle ages(30 - 50) are mot Affected
  • Cholesterol is the main factor for the Heart Disease
  • Blood Pressure and the Heart rate has impacts on Heart Disease which is impacted by cholesterol
  • Blood suger level has a light impact in heart disease
  • Most of the Induced Angina patients have Asymptomatic pain and Non anginal pain
  • Form the previous observation it is clear that Pain is not a symptom of Heart Disease
  • Upsloping at 0 oldpeak has the most Heat Disease Patients
